div.div: Fixed Single-instance EventBus in the Android App In this commit, a bug related to the Single-instance EventBus in the Android app has been fixed. This bug was causing the EventBus to create multiple instances in some scenarios. Now, the EventBus correctly maintains a single instance throughout the application, as intended.

Add calendar event functionality and change input type in ShopProductEdit
Implemented CRUD operations for calendar events in CalendarController and added permissions to the app's framework. Changed Quill input type to regular text area for product descriptions in ShopProductEdit for simplified configuration and enhanced user experience. New routes also added to api.php for these operations. A new table and model have been created to handle Calendar Events.

Update assignment of product tax in CustomerOrderConfirmed
The 'fetchProductTax' method in the 'CustomerOrderConfirmed' class is now directly assigned to the 'productTax' attribute. This better structures the code and improves readability.

Swap 'numeric' attribute from true to false in AttachmentLists
The 'numeric' attribute in the AttachmentLists.php file has been changed from true to false. This change could potentially affect how the count of Autumn files is displayed or interacted with.

Add unit constants and remove console log
The code has been updated to add BINARY_UNITS and METRIC_UNITS constants in AttachmentLists.php for improved file size representation. Also, an unnecessary console log in index.js that printed the ID value has been removed for better code cleanliness and performance.
